# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Aizen / ConversationAgent — environment template
#
# This file is COMMITTED and contains NO real secrets. It documents which keys
# the app expects. To use it:
#   1. Copy it to ".env"        (cp .env.example .env   /   Copy-Item .env.example .env)
#   2. Paste your real keys into ".env" (never into this file)
#   3. ".env" is gitignored, so your keys stay out of git.
#
# ⚠ NEVER paste a real key into .env.example, a prompt, a screenshot, or a chat.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Step 1 — Anthropic (real AI explanations).  console.anthropic.com
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Step 2 — Deepgram (real speech-to-text, streaming key).  deepgram.com
DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=

# Step 3 — Web search (sourced background / fact-checking, Channel D).
# Provider-abstracted (WebSearchProvider). Default provider: Tavily — tavily.com
# Set WEB_SEARCH_PROVIDER to switch adapters later (e.g. tavily | brave).
WEB_SEARCH_PROVIDER=tavily
TAVILY_API_KEY=
# BRAVE_API_KEY=        # uncomment if/when you swap the provider to Brave

# ── App server (all optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Port the local web app listens on (default 5173).
# PORT=5173
# Tenant UUID stamped on envelopes (default: the built-in dev tenant).
# TENANT_ID=

# Notes on modes:
#   • No DEEPGRAM_API_KEY → the app runs in DEMO mode (a canned clip drives the
#     pipeline) so you can see it work without a mic key.
#   • With ANTHROPIC_API_KEY but no Deepgram key, the demo card is still explained
#     by the REAL model.
#   • With BOTH keys → LIVE mode: speak into your mic, get real explanations.
